				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<DIV>The reason I have not done the group access in GoD has nothing to do with an unwillingness to use a hard, group-based alternative.&nbsp; It has to do with the fact that the hard, group-based alternative was designed for characters who already have raid-level access to zones, and thus equipment, that make GoD trials viable.&nbsp; To compare this to planar access, or to claim that such alternatives are available and not used because of this is off the mark.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The point is, there is NO hard, group-based alternative to accessing the elemental planes, and as of yet, no valid argument why there shouldn't be.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>To their credit, SOE has made it possible to gain equipment to make GoD viable for non-time/elemental geared players with many of the drops in groupable areas in OOW.&nbsp;&nbsp; This has corrected much of the urgency for fixing the flagging/backflagging issue, but it hasn't eliminated the issue.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And as to charming in GoD..why is that insane?&nbsp; Nothing crazy about using a pet that quad-taps for 1048 1048 1048 1048.&nbsp; The insane thing is that they allow that.&nbsp; It should be corrected (not in the halfassed way the nerfed it in OOW but in a well-thought out way) but it's a very valid way to go through these zones if you know what you're doing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
				
